Bluetooth: btusb/btmtk: compat fixes for pre-7.0 kernels

This DKMS package extracts btusb.c and btmtk.c from the kernel 7.0
tarball but is compiled against the host kernel, which is commonly
6.1 LTS through 6.19.x (CachyOS, Fedora 43, Ubuntu, Bazzite, etc.).

Two compat issues arise:

1. kmalloc_obj() / kzalloc_obj() (commit 2932ba8d9c99 "slab: Introduce
   kmalloc_obj() and family", adopted treewide in 69050f8d6d07). These
   helpers live only in kernel 7.0+ include/linux/slab.h. On pre-7.0
   hosts the build fails:

     btusb.c: error: call to undeclared function 'kmalloc_obj'
     btusb.c: error: call to undeclared function 'kzalloc_obj'
     btmtk.c: error: call to undeclared function 'kmalloc_obj'

   Replace the three call sites with kmalloc/kzalloc equivalents.
   kmalloc_obj(*x) expands to kmalloc(sizeof(*x), GFP_KERNEL) upstream,
   so behavior is identical. All three sites are sleepable.

2. hci_discovery_active() was exported for modules only in v7.0 by
   commit 97eb023cd161 ("Bluetooth: hci_core: Export
   hci_discovery_active"). v7.0 btusb.c calls it in btusb_suspend() via
   commit 312b09bbe983 ("Bluetooth: btusb: Reject autosuspend if
   discovery is active"). On pre-7.0 hosts, modpost fails:

     ERROR: modpost: "hci_discovery_active" [btusb.ko] undefined!

   Drop the discovery_active check from btusb_suspend(). This restores
   the behavior that shipped with in-tree btusb.c in kernel < 7.0 (no
   regression for the target audience). On kernel 7.0+ hosts a minor
   optimization is lost - USB autosuspend may fire during discovery -
   but those users would typically use the in-tree driver anyway.

Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>

diff --git a/btusb.c b/btusb.c
--- a/btusb.c
+++ b/btusb.c
@@ -2071,7 +2071,7 @@
 	if (!urb)
 		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
 
-	dr = kmalloc_obj(*dr);
+	dr = kmalloc(sizeof(*dr), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!dr) {
 		usb_free_urb(urb);
 		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
@@ -4062,7 +4062,7 @@
 			return -ENODEV;
 	}
 
-	data = kzalloc_obj(*data);
+	data = kzalloc(sizeof(*data), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!data)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
@@ -4481,8 +4481,7 @@
 	/* Don't auto-suspend if there are connections or discovery in
 	 * progress; external suspend calls shall never fail.
 	 */
-	if (PMSG_IS_AUTO(message) &&
-	    (hci_conn_count(data->hdev) || hci_discovery_active(data->hdev)))
+	if (PMSG_IS_AUTO(message) && hci_conn_count(data->hdev))
 		return -EBUSY;
 
 	if (data->suspend_count++)
diff --git a/btmtk.c b/btmtk.c
--- a/btmtk.c
+++ b/btmtk.c
@@ -537,7 +537,7 @@
 	if (!urb)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
-	dr = kmalloc_obj(*dr);
+	dr = kmalloc(sizeof(*dr), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!dr) {
 		usb_free_urb(urb);
 		return -ENOMEM;
